        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 3:53AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 353 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Litchfield, or 31 miles north of Kearney, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Hazard around 400 AM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Ravenna, Rockville,
Howard City and Boelus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
